HEADWORD: Polyphone
<hw>Pol"y*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A character or
vocal sign representing more than one sound, as <xex>read</xex>, which
is pronounced <xex>r⟦emac⟧d</xex> or <xex>r⟦ecr⟧d</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyphonic</ent>⟦br⟧
